	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540377_01.jpg"/>
			<p>Testimony</p>
			<p>Given by <persName ref="#ehri_et_strazshi_yoffe_sonya">Sonya Yofe</persName> born in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilna</placeName>, <date when="1946-09-17">17.IX.1946</date>.</p>
			<p>Recorded by <persName ref="#ehri_et_levental_nachman">Levental Nachman</persName></p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> of <placeName ref="#ehri_et_kailis"
					>Kailis</placeName> was as follows: two blocks on <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html"
					>Rydz-Śmigły</placeName> Street, where Jewish hat-makers lived and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term>. There were around 2000 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> there, who <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> at fur-hat making. The entire time it
				was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">relatively good</term>. The last period, in
					<date when="1944-06">June 1944</date>, they took fifty <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207"
					type="subject">people</term>, strong <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>,
				to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/506699/ponar.html">Ponar</placeName> to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> and they never came back. On <date
					when="1944-03-27">March 27, 1944</date>, they gathered together the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>, young and old <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">dressed</term> them neatly and took them to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282" type="subject">hospital</term>, ostensibly for an inspection – they
				took them through one door and out through another. There stood ready <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term>
				and <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanians</term> in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1091" type="subject">uniforms</term> with machine guns. And they took all
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> with the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mothers</term> and the old people, flinging them into
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">trucks</term> – they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transported</term> them through <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/598316/kaunas.html">Kovno</placeName>.</p>
			<p>After the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">Children’s</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">Action</term> [Kinder Aktion], a month later, they
				liquidated the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> of <placeName
					ref="#ehri_et_kailis">Kailis</placeName>. Some they sent to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html"
					>Riga</placeName>, and some to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598286/kazlu-ruda.html">Kazlova-Ruda</placeName>
					[<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598286/kazlu-ruda.html">Kazlų Rūda</placeName>], eighty <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> with a profession to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/598316/kaunas.html">Kovno</placeName>. Only 400 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> remained in <placeName
					ref="#ehri_et_kailis">Kailis</placeName>. They were only in <placeName ref="#ehri_et_kailis">Kailis</placeName> for another two
				weeks. Ten days before the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberation</term>, they
				took all the Jews, among them doctors <persName ref="#ehri_et_feyglis">Feyglis</persName> and Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_burak"
					>Burak</persName>, Eng. <persName ref="#ehri_et_pap">Pap</persName> (they did not let themselves be taken – they were dragged out
				to the trucks with force). They took them to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/506699/ponar.html">Ponar</placeName> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> them there. On the day of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberation</term>, when the Jews of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilna</placeName> who were in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">hiding places</term> came to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/506699/ponar.html">Ponar</placeName> at night, they found the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">photographs</term> and many <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">Jews lying unburied</term> in their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term> – because they [the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>] were hurrying and did not manage to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-746" type="subject">bury</term> them.</p>
			<p>Signed: <persName ref="#ehri_et_strazshi_yoffe_sonya">Sonya Strazshi-Yoffe</persName></p>
